Get() vs navigate();
both serves the same purpose --> to navigate to a particular url

get()--> u can't go back or forward in history
navigate()--> u can go back and forward and also refresh

get()--> it waits for the whole page to load
navigate()--> it doesn't wait for the whole page to load

close()--> t is going to close the current tab
quit()--> it is going to quit the whole driver session